{
  "message": "fuzz(mvcc-operations): 15 structured seeds for commit/abort/policy paths\n\nfuzz_mvcc_operations drives MvccStore through transaction lifecycles,\nall three commit paths (commit / commit_ssi / commit_fcw_prechecked),\nboth MergeProof variants, three ConflictPolicy values, and asserts\nfour invariants (monotonic commit_seq, snapshot isolation, post-\ncommit visibility, policy resolution). Existing 4 ad-hoc seeds\ncovered only the simplest commit happy path.\n\nAdds 15 seeds spanning every meaningful op-mix:\n\n  Lifecycle and commit paths:\n  * begin-only loop with no commits (active-txn cap + I4 invariant\n    in every iteration)\n  * basic begin \u2192 stage_write \u2192 commit, repeated 4\u00d7\n  * all three commit-path variants in one run (commit, commit_ssi,\n    commit_fcw_prechecked) \u2014 each with its own block + tag\n  * stage_write_with_proof using both MergeProof::Unsafe and\n    MergeProof::DisjointBlocks\n  * abort path: stage + abort + new txn + stage + commit\n  * MAX_ACTIVE_TXNS (16) concurrent transactions before any commit\n\n  Snapshot isolation (I2/I3):\n  * snapshot capture before, between, and after commits\n  * snapshot interleaved with multiple commit kinds + prune\n\n  Policy coverage:\n  * policy_toggle_lifecycle: cycles through Strict \u2192 SafeMerge \u2192\n    Adaptive \u2192 Strict, committing in each phase\n  * SafeMerge initial policy with three commit-path variants\n  * Adaptive initial policy\n\n  Block-domain coverage:\n  * full BLOCK_DOMAIN (8 blocks) touched by one transaction\n  * two writers staging the same block (concurrent-write conflict\n    surface)\n\n  Mixed finalisation:\n  * stage on 4 transactions, commit oldest, abort newest, commit_ssi,\n    commit_fcw_prechecked the remainder\n  * prune_after_commits: 8 commits then prune to verify post-prune\n    visibility invariant\n\nValidated by a 16 s libFuzzer run: 3 324 executions over the new\ncorpus (each run drives a real MvccStore + oracle, so throughput is\nsingle-digit-thousands), no crashes.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>",
